Argentine Stocks: Siderar SAIC, Telecom Argentina, YPF Advance

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-06-21T15:42:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/argentine-stocks-siderar-saic-telecom-argentina-ypf-advance.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 11:27 a.m. New York time.  The Merval Index rose 1.7 percent to 3,325.08.  Siderar SAIC (ERAR)  ,  Argentina ’s largest steel producer,
gained 3.7 percent to 31 pesos, its highest price in a month.
“Investors are showing more optimism for the second half of the
year and buying the bigger names in our stock market,” said
Alberto Tarsia, a trader at Buenos Aires-based Debursa Soc. de
Bolsa SA.  Telecom Argentina SA (TECO2 AF), Argentina’s second-largest
telephone company, advanced 4.4 percent, its biggest intraday
gain since November, to 22.40 pesos.  YPF SA (YPFD)  , the
Argentine unit of  Spain ’s Repsol YPF, rose 1.8 percent to 186
pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
 llazaroff@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
